SRBDF Configuration
Spatiotemporal Radar Backscatter Data Fusion for Antarctic Ice Shelves

Methodological Basis:
- Core framework: FSDAF (Zhu et al., 2016, A flexible spatiotemporal method for fusing satellite images with different resolutions. Remote Sens. Environ. 172, 165â€“177. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.rse.2015.11.016.)
- Source code: https://xiaolinzhu.weebly.com/open-source-code.html
- Present work: Migration to active microwave data
- Scientific application: Antarctic Ice Shelves surface melt monitoring
- Technical adaptation: Parameter optimization for radar backscatter

# Spatial parameters
w = 10                    # Half window size (full window = 2*w + 1 = 21)
scale_factor = 20         # Scale factor: coarse_res/fine_res (4km/200m = 20)
block_size = 20           # Processing block size in coarse pixels

# Similar pixel parameters
num_similar_pixel = 20    # Number of similar pixels
num_pure = 100            # Number of purest coarse pixels per class

# Classification parameters
min_class = 3.0           # Minimum number of classes
max_class = 4.0           # Maximum number of classes

# Data range parameters
DN_min = -30.0            # Minimum value of backscatter data
DN_max = 10.0             # Maximum value of backscatter data

# Processing parameters
background = -9999        # Background value
background_band = 1       # Single-band data configuration
temp_file = './temp'      # Temporary file directory
